Section 01:
Warm-up:

1. Neck rotation × 30 Sec
2. Shoulder Rotation (Clockwise and Anticlockwise) × 30 Sec
3. Arm rotation (Clockwise and Anticlockwise) × 30 Sec
4. Hip Rotation (Clockwise Anti-Clockwise) ×30 Sec
5. Lower Back & Hamstring ×30 Sec
6. Standing Toe Touh (Right) ×30 Sec
7. Standing Toe Touh (Left) ×30 Sec.
8. Side Lunge Pulse ×30 Sec
9. Knee to Chest ×30 Sec
10. Squat Rotations Reach the Sky ×30 Sec

Rest For 50 Seconds.

Section 02
Upper Body:
(Each Workout duration is 30 Secs followed by 30 Secs of Rest Time)

1. Pike Walkouts ×30 Sec
2. In and Out Push up ×30 Sec
3. Low Plank to High Plank ×30 Sec
4. Regular Pushups ×30 Sec
5. Burpees ×30 Sec
6. Plank Shoulder Tap ×30 Sec
7. Pike Pushups ×30 Sec
8. Diamond Pushups ×30 Sec

Rest for 60 Sec

Section 03
Lower body:
(Each Workout duration is 30 Secs followed by 30 Secs of Rest Time)

1. Squat Jump ×30 Sec
2. Alt Side Lunges ×30 Sec
3. Alt Front Lunges ×30 Sec
4. Squat Walk Outs ×30 Sec
5. Bridges ×30 Sec
6. Alt Curtsy Lunges ×30 Sec
7. In and Out Squat ×30 Sec
8. Squat Hold ×30 Sec

Rest For 60 Second

Section 04
Core:
(Each Workout duration is 30 Secs followed by 30 Secs of Rest Time)

1. Star Crunches ×30 Sec
2. Bicycle Kicks ×30 Sec
3. Lying Leg Raises ×30 Sec
4. Regular Crunches ×30 Sec
5. Reverse Crunches ×30 Sec
6. Leg Scissors ×30 Sec
7. Alt L-Sit Toe Touches ×30 Sec
8. Plank Hold ×30 Sec

Rest for 60 Sec

Section 05
HIIT
(Each Workout duration is 30 Secs followed by 30 Secs of Rest Time)

1. High Knees ×30 Sec
2. Criss Cross Oblique Crunch ×30 Sec
3. Mountain Climbers ×30 Sec
4. Jumping Jacks ×30 Sec
5. Butt Kicks 🤭 ×30 Sec
6. Squat Hold Punches ×30 Sec
7. Side To Side Run Touch The Floor ×30 Sec
8. Fast Feet ×30 Sec

××××××××××End Of Workout××××××××××

For anyone who wants my workout routine I'll tell you it's wayyy more effective first thing first you gotta eat calories dense food like avocado brown rice stuff like that and avoid fast food (but you can eat it once a week or so)
Here's my workout, btw warm up first this is very important (no equipment for Monday I called it chest day do 15 push up and rest 30 second then do 14 and rest 30 sec and do it until 10, in total it will be 75 push up (if it's too hard do knees push up)
Tuesday, Core day
Mountain climbers x40 each side
Hallow body hold 30-40 second
"How to perform hollow body hold lift your legs and lift your torso and keep your hand straight at the leg direction "you can search how to do it if you don't understand
Russian twist x24 each side
Leg raises x20
Leg scissor 25-40 second
Plank 1 minutes
Bicycle kick 40 each side
Whole body crunch x15
Sit up x25
Sorry if it's too ruthless:p you can adjust it on your own like 10 sit up instead of 25
Tuesday legs day
Jump squats x20
Weight squats x15(you can use heavy bag pack or something heavy but make sure it's not too heavy)
In and out squat x20
Squat hold 40 second
Burpees x20
Do it again or rest
Thursday cardio
You have two option first running second hitt
For running do this workout it increases your growth hormone, and increases testosterone
Sprint with your full speed for 30-40 second rest 90 second 5 set
For hitt just do what the video did, or you can also jump rope
Friday upper body
Push up x12
Diamond push up x12
Chair dip x20 (place both of your hand on the hair make sure you butt is the same level as the chair pretend your doing l sit but your leg stay on the ground and dip down then up that count as 1 rep)
Crocodile push up x12
Pike push up x12
Burpees x12
Saturday and Sunday are rest day
Guys after every week you can increases by 1 in every exercise like 13 instead of 12.
And for the chest day keep increasing until you did 15 to 1 push up then increases it to 20 until 10 and gradually increases it to 1 and after that you can add 10 more, something like that
